The weighted entropy of the two split nodes is 0.72. To get the information gain, subtract it from the entropy of the node that was split, in this case the root.

def information_gain(X, y, left_indices, right_indices):
    """
    Here, X has the elements in the node and y is their respective classes.
    """
    p_node = sum(y) / len(y)
    h_node = entropy(p_node)
    w_entropy = weighted_entropy(X, y, left_indices, right_indices)
    return h_node - w_entropy

